        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2012-05-26T15:06:27Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Agency Conferences and Conventions Operating Under Necessary Transparency Act of 2012 or the ACCOUNT Act - Requires the head of a federal agency to: (1) approve in writing&nbsp;any conference costing more than $25,000, (2) approve such a conference only upon determining that it is necessary to the core mission of the agency, and (3) publish a summary on the agency website&nbsp;of the conference that includes the purpose and total cost of the conference and the cost per employee that attended the conference.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
